        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 7:29PM PDT by NWS Elko NV</headline>
        <description>At 728 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Midas, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Willow Creek Reservoir and Midas Mine.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
